  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 5 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 2 critical, 3 high, 4 medium, 30 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Vilnius (VNO/EYVI); plus 2 other bases. 4 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is fog / freezing fog, mist and low cloud base  — most notably around Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), London Luton (LTN/EGGW) and London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK). Network hotspots: Maastricht Aachen (MST/EHBK), Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Eindhoven (EIN/EHEH). Primary drivers: RVR limitations, very low visibility and low cloud base. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), London Luton (LTN/EGGW) and 9 others.",
